      <title outputclass="H3_1_9" class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">9.306</ph> Solicitation
requirements.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <p otherprops="Body" outputclass="Body" class="- topic/p ">Solicitations
containing a testing and approval requirement shall-</p>
         <ol id="d571e16" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li otherprops="abc" outputclass="H5_abc" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d585e20" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                   Provide, in the circumstance
where the contractor is to be responsible for the first article
approval testing-</p>
               <ol id="d571e26" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d585e30" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                         The performance or other characteristics
that the first article must meet for approval;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d585e39" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                         The detailed technical requirements
for the tests that must be performed for approval; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d585e48" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                         The necessary data that must
be submitted to the Government in the first article approval <ph rev="FAC 2019-02 March 27, 2019" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 9.306 by—
 a.  Removing from paragraph (a)(3) “test report.” and adding “test report;” in its place;
?>test <?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] Technical Amendments?>report;</ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="abc" outputclass="H5_abc" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d585e65" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                   Provide, in the circumstance
where the Government is to be responsible for the first article
approval testing-</p>
               <ol id="d571e65" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d585e75" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                         The performance or other characteristics
that the first article must meet for approval; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d585e84" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                         The tests to which the first
article will be subjected <ph rev="FAC 2019-02 March 27, 2019" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [Why] b.  Removing from paragraph (b)(2) “for approval.” and adding “for approval;” in its place;?>for <?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] Technical Amendments?>approval;</ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="abc" outputclass="H5_abc" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d585e101" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                   Inform offerors that the requirement
may be waived when supplies identical or similar to those called
for have previously been delivered by the offeror and accepted by
the Government<ph rev="FAC 2019-02 March 27, 2019" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [Why] c.  Removing from paragraph (c) “(see 52.209-3(h) and 52.209-4(i);” and adding “(see 52.209-3(h) and 52.209-4(i));” in its place?>(see <xref href="FAR-i1062501.dita#i1062501"
                           base="i1062501"
                           outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                           class="- topic/xref ">52.209-3</xref>(h) <?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] Technical Amendments?>and <xref href="FAR-i1062528.dita#i1062528"
                           base="i1062528"
                           outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                           class="- topic/xref ">52.209-4</xref>(i))</ph>;</p>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="abc" outputclass="H5_abc" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d585e122" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
                   Permit the submission of alternative
offers, one including testing and approval and the other excluding
testing and approval (if eligible under <xref href="#i1115686"
                        base="i1115686"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">9.306</xref>(c));</p>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="abc" outputclass="H5_abc" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d585e134" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(e)</ph>
                   State clearly the first article’s
relationship to the contract quantity (see paragraph (e) of the
clause at <xref href="FAR-i1062501.dita#i1062501"
                        base="i1062501"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.209-3</xref>,
First Article Approval-Contractor Testing, or <xref href="FAR-i1062528.dita#i1062528"
                        base="i1062528"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.209-4</xref>,
First Article Approval-Government Testing);</p>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="abc" outputclass="H5_abc" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d585e150" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(f)</ph>
                   Contain a delivery schedule for
the production quantity <ph rev="FAC 2019-02 March 27, 2019" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [Why] d.  Removing from paragraph (f) “quantity (see 11.404)” and adding “quantity (see 11.403)” in its place;?>(see<?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] Technical Amendments?> <xref href="FAR-id1617MD00RFX.dita#id1617MD00RFX"
                           outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                           class="- topic/xref ">11.403</xref>)</ph>.
The delivery schedule may-</p>
               <ol id="d571e138" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d585e169" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                         Be the same whether or not testing
and approval is waived; or</p>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d585e178" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                         Provide for earlier delivery
when testing and approval is waived and the Government desires earlier
delivery. In the latter case, any resulting difference in delivery
schedules shall not be a factor in evaluation for award. The clause at <xref href="FAR-i1062528.dita#i1062528"
                              base="i1062528"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.209-4</xref>,
First Article Approval-Government Testing, shall contain the delivery
schedule for the first article;</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="abc" outputclass="H5_abc" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d585e192" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(g)</ph>
                   Provide for the submission of
contract numbers, if any, to document the offeror’s eligibility
under <xref href="#i1115686"
                        base="i1115686"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">9.306</xref>(c);</p>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="abc" outputclass="H5_abc" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d585e204" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(h)</ph>
                   State whether the approved first
article will serve as a manufacturing <ph rev="FAC 2019-02 March 27, 2019" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [Why] e.  Removing from paragraph (h) “and”; and?>standard;<?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] Technical Amendments?></ph>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="abc" outputclass="H5_abc" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d585e218" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                   Include, when the Government
is responsible for first article testing, the Government’s estimated
testing costs as a factor for use in evaluating offers <ph rev="FAC 2019-02 March 27, 2019" class="- topic/ph ">(when <?FM MARKER [Why] f.  Removing from paragraph (i) “(when appropriate).” and adding “(when appropriate); and” in its place.?>appropriate); <?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] Technical Amendments?>and</ph>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="abc" outputclass="H5_abc" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d585e234" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(j)</ph>
                   Inform offerors that the prices
for first articles and first article tests in relation to production
quantities shall not be materially unbalanced (see <xref href="FAR-i1106135.dita#i1106135"
                        base="i1106135"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">15.404-1</xref>(g))
if first article test items or tests are to be separately priced.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
